    "id": "steeltrace-partners-with-q-sys",
    "title": "SteelTrace partners with Q-Sys",
    "cat": "Company news",
    "author": "Tom Meulendijks",
    "role": "Expanding the ecosystem around SteelTrace",
    "date": "2020-05-06",
    "cover": 6,
    "image": "uploads/blog/steeltrace-partners-with-q-sys/hero.jpg",
    "preview": "uploads/blog/steeltrace-partners-with-q-sys/preview.jpg",
    "glyph": "NEWS",
    "body": "SteelTrace BV is pleased to announce its partnership with [Q-Sys Solutions](https://qsys-solutions.com/) to introduce and promote the use of our blockchain technology platform for material traceability and data integrity.\n\n\nOur CEO [Tom Meulendijks](https://www.linkedin.com/in/tommeulendijksmaastricht/) says: “SteelTrace can benefit from Q-Sys’ experience with quality management and network in Oil & Gas to accelerate our mission to remove friction and improving transparency in the supply chain of steel.” Q-Sys has over 20 years of experience in implementing ISO certifications, auditing of common ISO management systems such as 9001, 14001 and 45001 as well providing a full-service suite from initial supplier sourcing and evaluation through to product delivery. They work with companies like Subsea7, Lloyds Register, FTR and Barnshaws group.\n\n\nQ-Sys’ Technical Director, [Mark Walsh PCQI](https://www.linkedin.com/in/mark-walsh-cqp-mcqi-b09760b/) said “We believe that this innovative use of technology, coupled with our passion for quality within the supply chain, will present our shared Clients with a solution which provides complete confidence in material traceability, and the integrity of its associated data, whilst significantly reducing the time required to produce reports and material certificates. The technology can be utilised throughout the entire supply chain from steel production, steel product manufacture (such as plate, pipe, bends, flanges and fittings), testing laboratories as well as 2nd and 3rd party inspection agencies. Quality 4.0 has arrived, are you on-board?”\n\n\nWe are looking forward to working with Q-Sys.",
    "summary": "SteelTrace BV is pleased to announce its partnership with Q-Sys solutions to introduce and promote the use of our blockchain technology platform for material traceability and data integrity. Our CEO Tom Meulendijks says: “SteelTrace can benefit from Q-Sys’ experience with quality management and network in Oil & Gas to accelerate our mission to remove friction and improving transparency in the supply chain of steel.” Q-Sys has over 20 years of experience in implementing ISO certifications, auditing of common ISO management systems such as 9001, 14001 and 45001 as well providing a full-service suite from initial supplier sourcing and evaluation through to product delivery. They work with companies like Subsea7, Lloyds Register, FTR and Barnshaws group.",
    "slug": "steeltrace-partners-with-q-sys"
